\fs28 \cf0 Community
\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\fi720

\fs28 \cf0 - The community will centre around the Institute\'92s prime mechanic of Push Storytelling - bringing the story in a modular way to people through their chosen avenues. The community expands this out onto the web in a non-proprietary way, giving them a chance to push things to each other, as well. It creates a web instead of a pyramid ramp. 
\fs24 \

\fs28 - Media is a way to mediate human relations, anthropologically, and this is both the subject and goal of this experience.
\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\fi720

\b\fs28 \cf0 \
Experience Rather Than Text
\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\fi720

\fs28 \cf0 - The text is the medium, rather than the sale. The experience is wrapped in the interface, story, audio, 3D models, user tactility, community, discussion, and every aspect of what could be called Black Crown. They are important to the enjoyment, and to say \'93if you choose to pay, you are only paying to get text more quickly\'94 is very short-sighted. Signing up, also, needs to be very simple. 
\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\fi720

\b\fs28 \cf0 \
Dynamic Machine Reaction To Players
\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\fi720

\fs28 \cf0 - A game, an experience, cannot be static. It needs to react on every surface to player change and interaction. This is where the meta concerns of the project come into their own. The game, and we can react to how players are using to integrate the community into the craft of the thing.
\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\fi720

\b\fs28 \cf0 \
Slow Games
\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\fi720

\fs28 \cf0 - Slow games exist as part of life, with returnings to them, and the building of understanding, in a quotidian routine that allows contemplation instead of quickly-forgotten bursts of colour.
\fs24 \

\fs28 - I think a good quote to use is \'93slow purposeful accumulation of experiences\'94
\fs24 \

\fs28 - They should \ul \ulc0 want \ulnone to power through the content, but by imposing limits, we control the contemplation of the content, and it actually becomes an asset to be impatient, as it causes you to go and learn around the subject whilst you wait. 
